             TTI->getArithmeticInstrCost(
                 I->getOpcode(), VT, TCK_RecipThroughput,
                 TTI::OperandValue::getVarying(), TTI::OperandValue::getVarying());
  }
```

I need to replicate this logic inside `VPInstruction::computeCost`. In the VPlan world, `isUniform(V)` is the equivalent of the legacy `isUniform(I->getOperand(..))`. A `VPValue` is uniform if it's defined outside the vector region or is a `VPReplicateRecipe`. The `VPValue` class has an `isUniform()` method.

So, inside the `if (Instruction::isBinaryOp(getOpcode()))` block, I will add a check:
1. `if (Instruction::isShift(getOpcode()))`
2. Inside, check if either operand is uniform: `getOperand(0)->isUniform() || getOperand(1)->isUniform()`.
3. If so, return the special cost: `Ctx.TTI.getShuffleCost(...) + Ctx.TTI.getArithmeticInstrCost(...)`.
4. The type `VT` in the legacy model corresponds to `ResTy` here.

The `getShuffleCost` in the legacy model takes the instruction `I` as an argument, but the TTI interface doesn't always require it. The VPlan version will need to pass the appropriate arguments. `getShuffleCost` is defined as `getShuffleCost(ShuffleKind Kind, Type *Tp, ElementCount VF, Instruction *I = nullptr)`. I can pass `nullptr` for the instruction.

The final code will look something like this:
```cpp
  if (Instruction::isBinaryOp(getOpcode())) {
    if (!getUnderlyingValue()) {
      // ...
    }

    assert(...);
    Type *ResTy = Ctx.Types.inferScalarType(this);
    if (!vputils::onlyFirstLaneUsed(this))
      ResTy = toVectorTy(ResTy, VF);

    if (Instruction::isShift(getOpcode())) {
      if (getOperand(0)->isUniform() || getOperand(1)->isUniform()) {
        return Ctx.TTI.getShuffleCost(TargetTransformInfo::SK_Broadcast, ResTy,
                                      VF) +
               Ctx.TTI.getArithmeticInstrCost(
                   getOpcode(), ResTy, Ctx.CostKind,
                   TargetTransformInfo::OperandValue::getVarying(),
                   TargetTransformInfo::OperandValue::getVarying());
      }
    }

    return Ctx.TTI.getArithmeticInstrCost(getOpcode(), ResTy, Ctx.CostKind);
  }
```
